Creation & Branding - Promotion May 2022 - GP 2

Presentation

Talents across the LVMH Group create and develop products that perfectly embody the spirit of iconic Maisons and reflect the values of excellence, creativity, and innovation. In this module, you will gain an understanding of how ideas, products and concepts are born and brought to market. Moreover, you will have the opportunity to get key insights on brand management and how our passionate Talents build the long-term success of our Maisons.

Content:
• Creation as a key step for luxury brands
Deep dive into the creation process within the luxury and fashion industry with professors and immerse yourself into our Maisons; LVMH Talents from various business sectors will give you their strategic vision.

• Branding in the luxury industry
Get your keys to understand how to successfully manage a Brand in the luxury industry, from DNA and codes to marketing and concrete initiatives through testimonials of diverse Maisons.
Time to complete this section including a personal practice: approximately 2.5 hours

Chapters

Deep dive into Brand Management at Sephora

Brand differentiation and desirability.

Emmanuelle, could you please introduce yourself and your career path at LVMH, and particularly your role today at Sephora?

 

Driven by the passion for brands and consumers, and always animated by transformation projects, after almost 20 years spent in the Clothing industry at brands like Petit Bateau, I have joined the LVMH Group in 2013 as the Marketing & Offer Director for the French market at Sephora. 

 

This Maison has been offering me a new incredible and fast-paced environment, where I have discovered that beauty was a real playground all over the world with many possibilities. To me, Sephora is the best retailer ever, the only “Brand retailer”, a strong “House of Brands”, besides also being an incredibly innovative company.

 

Then, I had the chance to join Givenchy and Kenzo Parfums as International Retail and Sellout Director, before becoming the General Manager for France for 3 years. Finally, I had the pleasure to come back to Sephora in March 2020 as the Europe & Middle East Offer and Marketing General Manager. 


Today, my mission is to engage our clients and teams into the unlimited power of beauty. Sephora is known for its inclusive and desirable offer. Developing and extending this offer is an endless challenge, to make sure that we answer our clients’ needs. Creating new omnichannel shopping experiences, while building and maintaining strong relationships, is at the heart of our values. To sum up, we aim at constantly fueling our Brand differentiation and desirability.

What is your vision of brand management in the luxury industry, and then particularly at Sephora? 

 

Every single company is unique. The environment we evolve in requires a strong analysis of the different factors that may affect your chances of success or failure. Taking into account these factors will help you to define the vision and management that are the most appropriate for the company. Hence, it is all about finding the right balance between these elements. At Sephora, we believe that the beauty industry is in constant change, and therefore we are willing to adapt our offer, our stores and the way we communicate with our clients as well. We’re lucky: we know our customers and are able to understand their insights. Our goal is to go beyond to always delight customers more than anyone else and go further than their expectations.


A RICH AND INCLUSIVE OFFER 
Sephora’s offering is diverse, varied and innovative - we count over 16 000 references in France including, make-up, skincare, haircare, fragrances, food supplements and many more. Today, our clients come to Sephora because they know they will find an offering that matches their needs. Inclusiveness has always been part of our core values.

 

Exclusive brands are also a differentiation lever. From Huda Beauty to Fenty Beauty, or lately Milk Makeup, Drunk Elephant and Rare Beauty, our clients are thrilled to find the newest brands on the market. Furthermore, the brands we work with develop exclusive references only for Sephora. It definitely makes the difference as a retailer when it comes to key specific periods: Christmas, Valentines’ day, Mothers’ day, Fathers’ day. Our clients are able to get unique products for their loved ones.

 

Our own brand, Sephora Collection – fun and innovative - also offers an extensive range of products (makeup, skincare, fragrance, and haircare) and collaborations in tune with its time. The latest collaboration between Sephora Collection & Richaard on the French market has been a great success. This collaboration gave us also the opportunity to support the LGBTQ+ community, as 1€ per palette sold was given to LE MAG Jeunes LGBT – a truly involved association acting for this community.

 

We have also decided to work on a new program called “GOOD FOR”, to go beyond expectations and trends. This program – officially launched in Europe in October 2020 – gives our customers the opportunity to identify references within different categories pairing with responsible criteria:

 

• The GOOD FOR YOU tag gathers all the make-up and skincare references composed with a minimum of 90% ingredients of natural origin. 
• The GOOD FOR A BETTER PLANET tag gathers all the references whose packaging is eco-designed or developed with sustainable materials. Refillable perfume references are also included in this category. 
• The GOOD FOR VEGAN tag includes all the “vegan friendly” references we have in store. These products are developed without ingredients of animal origin. 
• The GOOD FOR RECYCLING tag, is a transversal label reminding our clients that Sephora is not only collecting perfume bottles but also make-up and skincare packaging.

 

This program not only gives our clients more transparency on the products and ingredients chosen, but also on the way the packaging is sourced and recycled. It also represents the continuity of all our engagements started a long time ago via our Sephora Stands program.


THE FUTURE OF STORES  
Nowadays, clients are looking for real experiences and expertise while entering attractive stores. They want to be surprised and they want to discover new products, brands and tips, every time they visit a store. They also want to be guided in the best possible way to facilitate their shopping experience. 


At Sephora, we are convinced that a new retail is born, much more in line with its clients and its time. Having a rich and inclusive offer is important, but having appealing stores and services counts as well.

 
Therefore, for many years now, our clients have had the opportunity to visit our stores for a shopping session while receiving beauty treatments or flash makeovers. Our makeup and skincare bars are considered as the hot spots of each store, giving our clients the opportunity to enjoy a personalized skin diagnostic, a make-up lesson, or just to discuss with our Beauty advisors. The expertise of our teams is crucial to guide our clients. The more we are digital, the more our customers will be looking for human contact!

 

We also constantly need to adapt our services. Since the beginning of the pandemic last year, we have now relocated our Click&Collect service at the entrance of the stores, facilitating clients’ collect. They really appreciate it!


We still believe in stores, in physical interactions with our clients, in addition to our digital channels. We are convinced that the physical stores still have a great future ahead in the beauty industry, but it must be in constant innovation. Hence, we keep renovating and opening stores. For instance, in France, the Opera store opened at the end of 2020 in the heart of Paris, and we renovate others.


Today we are convinced that we must go ahead and continue on this track in order to always go beyond our clients’ expectations, whether they visit our stores or our website.

BEING OMNICHANNEL

In addition to the expert advice from our Beauty advisors in-store, the digital perspective has always had a very important dimension at Sephora. There is no boundary between the digital and physical worlds, it is a unique customer journey where every touchpoint is key and must be perfect for the best experience.


Whether it is on our website or social media, digital technology allows us to consolidate the very strong relationship we have with our clients and our community. The different lockdowns have also underlined the strong bond with have with them, as our online channels were the only ways to keep in touch. Our community is very engaged and always looking for new trends and the latest novelties. For instance, in France we just reached 2M followers on Instagram, which makes it one of the most engaged communities in France in the beauty industry.


Digitalisation has also enabled us to be one of the first retailers to give our clients the opportunity to book a cosmetic treatment online via our website, to get for instance their brows waxed at our Benefit Brow Bars located in-store. 


The pandemic has also accelerated the digitalisation in many aspects, especially online sales. It clearly highlights the need of being omni channel and of always taking into consideration the digital dimension. New projects combining the expertise of our Beauty Advisors and the precision of the digital tools were recently launched:  


• In-store Skin Diagnostic 
A smartphone application that allows our Beauty Advisors to diagnose our clients’ skin and recommend skincare products. The analysis is done using a lens placed on the objective of the advisor's smartphone, which will take a photo of 3 skin areas defined on the clients. This technology analyses the skin on different criteria: hydration, pores, sebum and wrinkles. Hence, our Beauty Advisors’ expertise is complementary to the tool as they will be able to precisely guide our clients to get them the most appropriate routine.

 

• Sephora Live Shopping 
This tool gives our website’s visitors the opportunity to speak live with our advisors in-store. This new technology has been developed by the end of 2020 and our clients love it since they are guided in their beauty search as if they were in our store. Advisors have the ability to send photos and record live videos for users to show them the products. The digital client experience has therefore been completely revised.

What are the key stakes and challenges for Sephora to become even more attractive and successful? 

We cannot deny that the past year has been a challenging one for everyone. Big and small companies have both faced the pandemic and the important changes associated. These changes were also important given the short notice period to take them into account. 
Many companies have had to deal with these questions: 

How to adapt ourselves to an unprecedented health crisis?
How to remain authentic to our cores values?
How to maintain the strong bond built with our teams and our clients?

While trying to find the right balance between some of the elements here below:

 

Agility
Under any circumstances, a company must remain flexible. The recent situation taught us how, at Sephora, we must be even more flexible and gain in adaptability. We were repeatedly forced to close our stores from one day to the other and re-adapt our supply chain in order to follow the growth of online orders. Adaptability gave us the opportunity to rethink our stores and warehouses and to respond efficiently to the growing demand we were facing.  

 

Authenticity … a brand with purpose
Nowadays, clients are looking for authentic brands with strong convictions, values and engagements. Many brands highlight their engagements because it is important to make sure these are known. However, only a few of them can pretend to be committed for a long time.  To not add but to act is today mandatory. 
At Sephora, we have implemented a program called “Sephora Stands” for many years now. This program gathers all our environmental and CSR engagements to provide equal chances for all communities.


We are proud to work with different associations abroad and in France such as Toutes à L’Ecole – supporting girls’ education in Cambodia; Force Femmes – supporting womens’ employment – and the association Women Safe & Children – supporting women and children victims of domestic violence.

 

Engaging our teams and clients 
Talents are so much more than just people completing their day-to-day tasks. They are the lifeblood of the company, and by far its more important success factor. At Sephora, we consider them as brand ambassadors, especially our Beauty Advisors, who are in direct contact with our clients. They convey our core values and share our common passion for beauty with the world. They are part of the clients’ shopping experience and we make sure that they can get the best training to be knowledgeable on our large offering to guide our clients efficiently. 
Clients love expertise and that is reason why they come to Sephora. 
The beauty power is in our hands, let’s spread it together!
